 According to the Quartz Africa Weekly Brief, the national bus service will look beyond Cairo to include other major governorates.
 Uber currently operates in the capital, which the second most populous African city at over 21 million people, as well as Alexandria and Mansoura. Cairo is one of Uber’s fastest growing markets with more than 30,000 drivers in 2016.
